LLMS full export

Purpose:
- Full AI-readable export pointer for the MemoryEndpoints.com UAIX package without duplicating all memory bodies.

Verification status: active operational export; verify with `.uai/exports/manifest.json` and the `.uai` audit before relying on it.
Memory scope: export map, package profile, memory boundaries, active read order, and durable evidence roots.
Public-safe status: safe for source control; contains no credential values.
Update route: refresh this export when package profile, active read order, durable roots, or public claim boundaries change.
Source of truth: `.uai/exports/manifest.json`, `.uai/startup-packet.uai`, `.uai/progress.uai`, `.uai/memory.uai`, and readiness reports.
Next action for agents: do not treat this export as a replacement for reading the active `.uai` files.
Must not expose: raw API keys, bearer tokens, FTP credentials, database passwords, private keys, private handoff payloads, raw one-time keys, raw private memory bodies, or private deployment values.

Package profile:
- Project Handoff.
- Agent File Handoff.
- Code-bearing project/developer package.
- MATM durable-memory routing through MemoryEndpoints.com.

Read first:
